1
00:00:01,269 --> 00:00:03,771
Previously on Lucifer...
He is so into you.

2
00:00:03,804 --> 00:00:05,339
You're joking.
Uh, no.

3
00:00:05,373 --> 00:00:08,242
Scorching fire, five-alarm.

4
00:00:08,276 --> 00:00:10,478
I can see why Lucifer
is so affected by you.

5
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:12,646
It's because you're
special, Decker.

6
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:14,748
Being a celestial insider...

7
00:00:14,782 --> 00:00:16,250
really sucks.

8
00:00:16,284 --> 00:00:19,353
I was in a really
dark place, but someone

9
00:00:19,387 --> 00:00:20,754
helped me gain perspective.

10
00:00:20,788 --> 00:00:23,457
LUCIFER: Now Maze is off
bounty hunting again.

11
00:00:23,491 --> 00:00:25,426
ELLA:
Being good takes practice.

12
00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:28,129
Keep at it
and you'll get better.

13
00:00:28,162 --> 00:00:29,663
I guess I should
take that job then.

14
00:00:29,697 --> 00:00:32,333
What job?
The Sinnerman is not a myth.

15
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:34,802
I butted heads with him in
Chicago. Did not end well.

16
00:00:34,835 --> 00:00:37,571
LUCIFER:
Not only did he stick my wings
back on and take my face,

17
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:39,440
he's stolen my schtick,
as well.

18
00:00:39,473 --> 00:00:40,841
He gives out favors to people.

19
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:42,376
And I think that maybe

20
00:00:42,410 --> 00:00:44,612
it's about time
I got back in the game.

21
00:00:45,713 --> 00:00:48,316
*

22
00:00:55,356 --> 00:00:57,858
* We are the way out

23
00:00:57,891 --> 00:01:00,294
* We are the ones you loathe

24
00:01:00,328 --> 00:01:02,730
* Call us the wrong crowd

25
00:01:02,763 --> 00:01:05,566
* We'll never walk alone

26
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:12,273
* Don't need no savior

27
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:13,407
* Don't need a hand...

28
00:01:13,441 --> 00:01:15,576
Line's back there, buddy.

29
00:01:15,609 --> 00:01:17,111
Is the, uh,

30
00:01:17,145 --> 00:01:18,612
big guy in tonight?

31
00:01:18,646 --> 00:01:20,848
* We have gone too far
to turn around *

32
00:01:20,881 --> 00:01:22,350
This is a one.

33
00:01:22,383 --> 00:01:24,318
* We move too fast
to keep us down *

34
00:01:24,352 --> 00:01:26,320
Nice guy discount?

35
00:01:26,354 --> 00:01:29,323
* We are, we are,
we are the reckless *

36
00:01:29,357 --> 00:01:30,724
Make it quick, kid.

37
00:01:31,892 --> 00:01:34,728
You're a prince.

38
00:01:34,762 --> 00:01:35,829
Thank you.

39
00:01:35,863 --> 00:01:38,166
*

40
00:01:38,199 --> 00:01:40,601
* The reckless

41
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:42,270
*

42
00:01:42,303 --> 00:01:45,239
* We are the reckless

43
00:01:47,808 --> 00:01:50,878
* Go on and chase us

44
00:01:50,911 --> 00:01:52,513
* We can't be caught, oh, no

45
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:54,215
* Call us contagious

46
00:01:54,248 --> 00:01:55,683
Hey.

47
00:01:55,716 --> 00:01:57,518
Uh, Mr. Morningstar?

48
00:01:57,551 --> 00:01:59,287
I hear you're the guy
to talk to.

49
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:01,222
I hear you help people.

50
00:02:01,255 --> 00:02:02,423
(laughs)
What, like Ellen?

51
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:03,524
(laughs)

52
00:02:03,557 --> 00:02:04,692
I think not.

53
00:02:04,725 --> 00:02:07,361
(laughs)

54
00:02:07,395 --> 00:02:09,363
No, I grant people favors.

55
00:02:09,397 --> 00:02:11,399
When it suits me.

56
00:02:11,432 --> 00:02:13,667
Well, I-I could use a favor.

57
00:02:15,303 --> 00:02:17,238
Hear me out, Mr. Morningstar.

58
00:02:17,271 --> 00:02:18,506
You won't regret it.

59
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:22,576
Victoria, give us a minute,
would you, girl?

60
00:02:22,610 --> 00:02:24,478
* Ain't no way
we're stopping now *

61
00:02:25,713 --> 00:02:28,649
* Ain't no way we're
stopping now *

62
00:02:28,682 --> 00:02:31,185
* We are, we are,
we are the reckless *

63
00:02:31,219 --> 00:02:32,653
Call me Lucifer.

64
00:02:32,686 --> 00:02:34,355
Joey Pileggi.

65
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:35,956
So, Joey Pileggi,

66
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,725
what is it you desire?

67
00:02:39,293 --> 00:02:41,262
LINDA: Okay, so,
how do you angels work?

68
00:02:41,295 --> 00:02:44,398
I know Amenadiel
can slow time,

69
00:02:44,432 --> 00:02:47,568
and your other brother Uriel
could predict patterns.

70
00:02:47,601 --> 00:02:50,304
So why is your
gift desire?

71
00:02:50,338 --> 00:02:51,839
(sighs) Well,

72
00:02:51,872 --> 00:02:53,541
that's a good question,
actually, I suppose.

73
00:02:53,574 --> 00:02:55,843
When I first went
to angel school,

74
00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:59,447
they sorted us into different
houses for different powers.

75
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,848
There's a school for angels?

76
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:03,484
No.
(laughs)

77
00:03:05,586 --> 00:03:07,555
(laughing):
There's no Hogwarts in the sky.

78
00:03:07,588 --> 00:03:10,324
(laughing):
Right. Obviously.

79
00:03:12,593 --> 00:03:16,330
Are you using humor to deflect
my very reasonable question?

80
00:03:16,364 --> 00:03:18,966
(sighs)
Look, if you must know,

81
00:03:18,999 --> 00:03:20,901
we were all born this way,

82
00:03:20,934 --> 00:03:23,003
each with our own
God-given abilities.

83
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,872
But what came first?

84
00:03:24,905 --> 00:03:28,476
Do angels' powers shape
their personalities?

85
00:03:28,509 --> 00:03:31,745
Or are your personalities
shaped by your powers?

86
00:03:31,779 --> 00:03:33,347
Haven't a clue.

87
00:03:34,648 --> 00:03:38,486
Look, all I know is that
my powers are perfect for me.

88
00:03:38,519 --> 00:03:40,654
Desire is the ultimate
expression of free will.

89
00:03:40,688 --> 00:03:44,358
I help people do whatever--
or whomever-- they want.

90
00:03:44,392 --> 00:03:46,394
But that's it?

91
00:03:47,528 --> 00:03:49,363
There isn't more to it?

92
00:03:50,631 --> 00:03:51,799
(sighs)

93
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,909
Sorry.
(clears throat)

94
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:04,545
I-I should have knocked.
It's a late night.

95
00:04:04,578 --> 00:04:05,813
Been trying to catch up
on all the work

96
00:04:05,846 --> 00:04:08,282
since I got out
of the hospital.

97
00:04:08,316 --> 00:04:09,917
Stole a couple hours
on the couch.

98
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:13,787
Um, thank you again...

99
00:04:13,821 --> 00:04:15,423
for saving my life.

100
00:04:15,456 --> 00:04:17,525
It's, uh...

101
00:04:17,558 --> 00:04:19,427
Looks like you're,
you're healing really well.

102
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:21,762
It still hurts
like a son of a bitch.

103
00:04:23,431 --> 00:04:24,565
You know what? I'll, um...

104
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:25,799
I'll just come back
another time.

105
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:27,768
Now's good. What do
you want, Decker?

106
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:34,808
Uh, I wanted to request
a personal day.

107
00:04:35,843 --> 00:04:37,044
What for?

108
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:38,546
Well, it's personal.

109
00:04:38,579 --> 00:04:40,681
I'll take it under advisement.

110
00:04:40,714 --> 00:04:42,950
I didn't think
it'd be an issue.

111
00:04:47,855 --> 00:04:50,090
CHLOE:
It's just one personal day.

112
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:51,892
I never ask for anything.

113
00:04:51,925 --> 00:04:53,594
You're too low-
maintenance, Detective.

114
00:04:53,627 --> 00:04:55,696
People assume work
is your only desire.

115
00:04:55,729 --> 00:04:57,064
Yeah, well, it's not.

116
00:04:57,097 --> 00:04:58,466
Yeah, what a jerk.

117
00:04:58,499 --> 00:05:00,368
Oh, look who's all
hot and bothered.

118
00:05:00,401 --> 00:05:01,902
Someone got under
your skin.

119
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:04,438
(chuckles) What do you want
with a personal day anyway?

120
00:05:04,472 --> 00:05:06,540
It's personal.

121
00:05:07,908 --> 00:05:12,446
(sighs) Looks like some sort of
poor man's penthouse, isn't it?

122
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,947
(camera snaps)
Hmm.

123
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:15,583
CHLOE:
Boy, he's young.

124
00:05:15,616 --> 00:05:18,018
Practically a kid.
ELLA: Yeah.

125
00:05:18,051 --> 00:05:21,589
What happened here?
Who would have done this?

126
00:05:21,622 --> 00:05:22,923
I'm afraid I might know.

127
00:05:25,025 --> 00:05:27,661
You see, I did
this young man a favor.

128
00:05:28,996 --> 00:05:30,931
*

129
00:05:39,006 --> 00:05:41,108
CHLOE:
Lucifer, can I talk to you?

130
00:05:43,777 --> 00:05:46,847
What exactly does this
have to do with you?

131
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,482
Well, his name's Joey.

132
00:05:48,516 --> 00:05:50,884
Joey Pileggi, he came
to me a few months ago

133
00:05:50,918 --> 00:05:53,086
and asked me for a favor,
and I granted it to him.

134
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,888
You're still doing that?
(laughs)

135
00:05:54,922 --> 00:05:57,691
I'd never stop
granting favors, Detective.

136
00:05:57,725 --> 00:06:00,694
I mean, I may have gotten
distracted for a while,

137
00:06:00,728 --> 00:06:02,496
but then I realized
granting favors defines me.

138
00:06:02,530 --> 00:06:05,032
I mean, you wouldn't ask
Superman not to fly?

139
00:06:05,065 --> 00:06:06,700
A Kardashian
not to selfie?

140
00:06:06,734 --> 00:06:08,902
So I started up again and it was
going splendidly, until...

141
00:06:08,936 --> 00:06:12,506
What kind of favor? And don't
tell me it got Joey killed.

142
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:15,509
Well, his desire was to become
the new Godfather,

143
00:06:15,543 --> 00:06:17,445
a Scarface for millennials.

144
00:06:17,478 --> 00:06:18,712
You introduced him to the mob?

145
00:06:18,746 --> 00:06:20,881
I may have gotten him
an internship.

146
00:06:20,914 --> 00:06:22,816
(indistinct police radio
chatter)

147
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:24,017
Ella.

148
00:06:24,051 --> 00:06:26,019
What do you have
on the cause of death?

149
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:27,655
Two gunshot wounds
to the chest,

150
00:06:27,688 --> 00:06:29,523
and his legs were broken.

151
00:06:29,557 --> 00:06:30,924
Practically
shattered.

152
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:33,527
But here's the weird part.
I thought that the killer

153
00:06:33,561 --> 00:06:35,429
broke Joey's legs first--
you know, torturing him

154
00:06:35,463 --> 00:06:36,997
before killing him--
but look.

155
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,766
Minimal hemorrhaging.

156
00:06:38,799 --> 00:06:40,100
That's when I realized

157
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,069
Joey's legs were
broken postmortem.

158
00:06:42,102 --> 00:06:45,473
Why? What's the killer
trying to say?

159
00:06:45,506 --> 00:06:46,807
(quietly):
Oh, no.

160
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:47,975
What?

161
00:06:48,008 --> 00:06:51,912
Well, it may be a commentary
on the job that I got for him.

162
00:06:53,046 --> 00:06:55,583
As a runner for the mob.

163
00:06:59,987 --> 00:07:02,956
(laughing): Angel school?
LINDA: Okay, what?

164
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,525
It's not that funny, okay.

165
00:07:04,558 --> 00:07:05,959
(laughing continues)

166
00:07:05,993 --> 00:07:08,762
Okay. Okay, it's
kind of funny.

167
00:07:08,796 --> 00:07:11,131
You really thought
angel school was a thing?

168
00:07:11,164 --> 00:07:12,800
How was I supposed to know?

169
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:13,734
What's crazier,

170
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,704
angel school, or that
you can slow time,

171
00:07:16,737 --> 00:07:18,906
or that Lucifer can draw
out people's desires?

172
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:21,174
Okay, I can see how
that would seem strange.

173
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:23,577
No, it's bananas,
Amenadiel.

174
00:07:23,611 --> 00:07:26,046
I mean, how does
any of it all work?

175
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,648
Like...

176
00:07:27,681 --> 00:07:31,919
why is your power
slowing down time?

177
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:33,954
(sighs)

178
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:36,590
Maybe my Father wanted me
to be a better emissary,

179
00:07:36,624 --> 00:07:38,492
someone who could
fix things on Earth

180
00:07:38,526 --> 00:07:40,193
and stay invisible.

181
00:07:40,227 --> 00:07:43,531
So, I can slow down time
and do His bidding

182
00:07:43,564 --> 00:07:45,933
without anyone being the wiser.

183
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:49,036
That seems really...

184
00:07:49,069 --> 00:07:50,604
sad.

185
00:07:50,638 --> 00:07:52,105
What do you mean?
I mean,

186
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:54,241
it... it just seems lonely

187
00:07:54,274 --> 00:07:58,879
to visit humanity without ever
really getting to know anyone.

188
00:08:00,113 --> 00:08:03,584
I guess I was never told
to avoid humanity.

189
00:08:05,586 --> 00:08:07,555
It just seemed easier.

190
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:11,692
And quite honestly,
I never saw the point.

191
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,562
Until recently.

192
00:08:16,096 --> 00:08:18,265
Hey, stranger...

193
00:08:18,298 --> 00:08:19,567
LINDA:
Maze!

194
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,602
You're back!
Yeah!

195
00:08:21,635 --> 00:08:23,537
Oh, I missed you,
too, girl.

196
00:08:23,571 --> 00:08:25,939
Where was your bounty
this time, Mazikeen?

197
00:08:25,973 --> 00:08:27,074
Uh, Cleveland.

198
00:08:27,107 --> 00:08:28,809
(sighs): Now I'm
banned in Ohio.

199
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:31,144
Ah.
So, uh, what's
going on?

200
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:32,813
What are you
guys up to?

201
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:33,881
(laughs)

202
00:08:33,914 --> 00:08:35,215
Okay. Well, Linda...

203
00:08:35,248 --> 00:08:38,251
Linda was just catching me up
on how sh...

204
00:08:38,285 --> 00:08:42,022
(laughs): on how she believed
in "angel school."

205
00:08:42,055 --> 00:08:43,824
(chuckles):
Oh.

206
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:47,160
You... guys
catch up, huh?

207
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:49,563
Yes. Yeah, we...
we've been hanging out.

208
00:08:49,597 --> 00:08:50,998
Yeah, we're friends.

209
00:08:52,099 --> 00:08:53,601
Right.

210
00:08:54,668 --> 00:08:56,737
Right. Friends.
(chuckles)

211
00:08:57,871 --> 00:08:59,840
ELLA: It's not
just any shoe.

212
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:01,975
Joey's high-tops were
limited edition.

213
00:09:02,009 --> 00:09:03,877
Easily worth
a grand a pair.

214
00:09:03,911 --> 00:09:06,079
I mean, my brothers
would flip over these.

215
00:09:06,113 --> 00:09:07,615
Sweet kicks indeed.

216
00:09:07,648 --> 00:09:09,116
Sorry I'm late.

217
00:09:09,149 --> 00:09:10,317
CHLOE:
Charlotte.

218
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,819
What are you
doing here?

219
00:09:11,852 --> 00:09:13,220
Little early for
opposing counsel.

220
00:09:13,253 --> 00:09:14,221
Are you defending
someone?

221
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:15,589
CHARLOTTE:
No.

222
00:09:15,623 --> 00:09:16,824
I quit my job.

223
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:18,992
Oh. Well, good for you,
Charlotte.

224
00:09:19,026 --> 00:09:20,360
Had enough of life

225
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:21,962
as a corrupt defense
lawyer, have you?

226
00:09:21,995 --> 00:09:23,831
That'll help keep
your ledger clear.

227
00:09:23,864 --> 00:09:26,266
Today is my first day in the
district attorney's office--

228
00:09:26,299 --> 00:09:27,968
as a prosecutor.

229
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:29,202
I'm on your side now.

230
00:09:29,236 --> 00:09:30,938
Surprise.
(chuckles)

231
00:09:30,971 --> 00:09:31,739
Did you know about this?

232
00:09:31,772 --> 00:09:33,974
Not a clue.
How did this happen?

233
00:09:34,007 --> 00:09:36,009
Who knows
how these things happen?

234
00:09:36,043 --> 00:09:37,577
So random.

235
00:09:38,746 --> 00:09:40,213
Guess we should get back
to the case, right?

236
00:09:40,247 --> 00:09:42,149
Right.
Right.

237
00:09:42,182 --> 00:09:44,952
So, Joey had expensive shoes,

238
00:09:44,985 --> 00:09:46,186
plus...

239
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:47,855
a real Rolex

240
00:09:47,888 --> 00:09:51,725
and ten grand stashed
under his bed.

241
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:52,926
But Joey worked for the mob.
I mean,

242
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,695
wouldn't that explain
all the swag?

243
00:09:54,728 --> 00:09:56,396
Runners for the mob
don't make that kind of money.

244
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:58,031
There's no way
he could afford that.

245
00:09:58,065 --> 00:10:00,634
Maybe Joey was skimming
off the top.

246
00:10:01,669 --> 00:10:03,136
No, you don't have to
raise your hand.

247
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:06,006
Okay, well, um, his bosses
wouldn't like that.

248
00:10:06,039 --> 00:10:06,974
They would
execute Joey

249
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:09,076
to send a message to
the whole organization.

250
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:11,278
Whoever brought him in
would do the deed.

251
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:12,980
Lovely.

252
00:10:13,013 --> 00:10:14,948
What? I know
how these guys work.

253
00:10:14,982 --> 00:10:17,284
I've represented mobsters
like this for years.

254
00:10:17,317 --> 00:10:19,687
Alleged mobsters.

255
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:22,790
(sighs) Who did you
introduce Joey to?

256
00:10:22,823 --> 00:10:24,658
Frankie the Knife.
Sweet chap.

257
00:10:24,692 --> 00:10:25,926
Sounds like
a peach.

258
00:10:25,959 --> 00:10:27,160
CHLOE: All right,
let's bring in Frankie

