278
00:11:26,286 --> 00:11:28,221
This is a mistake.

279
00:11:30,357 --> 00:11:32,125
Okay.

280
00:11:32,159 --> 00:11:35,462
Okay.

281
00:11:35,495 --> 00:11:38,231
Okay. I'm so sorry, Linda.

282
00:11:45,272 --> 00:11:48,375
Detective, Lucifer.
Are you about to talk

283
00:11:48,408 --> 00:11:50,077
to Frankie the Knife?
Yep.

284
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:52,045
Well, I can help. I know him.
(phone vibrates)

285
00:11:52,079 --> 00:11:53,280
I defended him once.

286
00:11:53,313 --> 00:11:54,481
Unknown caller?

287
00:11:54,514 --> 00:11:56,083
Um...

288
00:11:56,116 --> 00:11:58,986
Look, why don't you give
the newbie a shot, Detective.

289
00:11:59,019 --> 00:12:01,054
I mean, I for one would love an
audience when I ream Frankie

290
00:12:01,088 --> 00:12:01,989
for what he did.

291
00:12:02,022 --> 00:12:04,157
No one will be reaming anyone.

292
00:12:04,191 --> 00:12:06,126
Fine, Charlotte.

293
00:12:06,159 --> 00:12:07,427
Just keep a low profile.

294
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:08,962
You won't even know I'm there.

295
00:12:10,163 --> 00:12:12,165
Hello, Frankie.

296
00:12:12,199 --> 00:12:14,835
Mr. Ferrante.
I'm Detective Decker.

297
00:12:14,868 --> 00:12:16,970
We know each other quite
well, don't we, Frankie?

298
00:12:17,004 --> 00:12:18,772
Not sure we've met, buddy.

299
00:12:18,806 --> 00:12:20,073
Oh, please.

300
00:12:20,107 --> 00:12:21,909
And this is...
Charlotte Richards?

301
00:12:21,942 --> 00:12:24,177
How are you?
How are the kids?

302
00:12:24,211 --> 00:12:25,478
Hi, Frankie.

303
00:12:25,512 --> 00:12:27,080
Man, the guys
are sure gonna be jealous

304
00:12:27,114 --> 00:12:28,448
