Try not to gloat too much.

487
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:14,954
Oh, easy, Decker.
What's the rush?

488
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:16,289
Hey, Lieutenant.

489
00:19:16,323 --> 00:19:18,225
Um, so Ella found
the Sinnerman's DNA

490
00:19:18,258 --> 00:19:20,260
at both scenes,
and I think we can use that

491
00:19:20,293 --> 00:19:21,594
to lean on Frankie Ferrante.

492
00:19:21,628 --> 00:19:23,230
That's promising.

493
00:19:23,263 --> 00:19:24,664
Where's Lucifer?
You need help?

494
00:19:24,697 --> 00:19:25,798
I mean, I'm free.

495
00:19:25,832 --> 00:19:27,867
Oh, um...

496
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:31,438
Oh, I'm-I'm good,
thanks. I'm, um...

497
00:19:31,471 --> 00:19:33,906
I'm okay. I'm gonna...
I'm gonna take Charlotte.

498
00:19:35,842 --> 00:19:37,877
I'm sensing some tension here.

499
00:19:37,910 --> 00:19:39,679
Really?

500
00:19:39,712 --> 00:19:41,681
I'm not.

501
00:19:41,714 --> 00:19:43,616
I haven't forgotten about your
request for a personal day.

502
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:45,452
Things have been crazy here.
I just haven't had a chance

503
00:19:45,485 --> 00:19:47,554
to look at the schedule yet.
Yeah. No. All good.

504
00:19:47,587 --> 00:19:48,888
I haven't been thinking
about that.

505
00:19:48,921 --> 00:19:50,323
I-I'm actually gonna
take Charlotte

506
00:19:50,357 --> 00:19:51,924
'cause she's perfect for this.

507
00:19:51,958 --> 00:19:54,361
Keep me posted.

508
00:19:54,394 --> 00:19:55,662
Mm-hmm.

509
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:58,698
You needed me, Detective?

510
00:19:58,731 --> 00:19:59,799
Sure do.

511
00:19:59,832 --> 00:20:01,434
Let's go.

