00:20:32,499 --> 00:20:34,000
Where are you?

521
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:37,470
* The dust has settled

522
00:20:37,504 --> 00:20:40,573
The slaughterhouse vibe
is a little try-hard,

523
00:20:40,607 --> 00:20:41,841
don't you think?

524
00:20:41,874 --> 00:20:45,044
*

525
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,480
You know,
it's quite the party foul

526
00:20:47,514 --> 00:20:49,616
when the host
doesn't even show up!

527
00:20:49,649 --> 00:20:51,618
SINNERMAN:
In here.

528
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:57,290
Ah, so what is it,
hide-and-seek now?

529
00:20:59,792 --> 00:21:02,562
* Cold, cold blood

530
00:21:02,595 --> 00:21:05,832
Come on, let's talk.

531
00:21:05,865 --> 00:21:09,369
That is, if you're
man enough to face me!

532
00:21:09,402 --> 00:21:12,472
* Cold, cold blood.

533
00:21:16,676 --> 00:21:19,679
SINNERMAN:
I do love a captive audience.

534
00:21:25,818 --> 00:21:28,521
Oh.

535
00:21:29,989 --> 00:21:31,691
Well played.

536
00:21:36,396 --> 00:21:39,466
It's a pleasure
to finally meet you.

537
00:21:39,499 --> 00:21:41,067
Likewise.

538
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,770
Always gratifying to find out
that one's nemesis

539
00:21:43,803 --> 00:21:45,838
is altogether lacking
in style.

540
00:21:45,872 --> 00:21:47,073
Never been much
of a dresser.

541
00:21:47,106 --> 00:21:49,108
I express myself
through my work.

542
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:52,412
I take it you're referring
to Frieda and Joey.

543
00:21:52,445 --> 00:21:54,581
Why harm them
when you wanted me?

544
00:21:54,614 --> 00:21:58,585
Well, you can't have a trap
without bait,

545
00:21:58,618 --> 00:22:01,020
can you, now?

546
00:22:01,053 --> 00:22:05,091
I hate to toot my own horn,
but I got you good.

547
00:22:05,124 --> 00:22:06,559
Yes, indeed you did.

548
00:22:06,593 --> 00:22:08,695
Quite the mousetrap
you've laid out for me.

549
00:22:08,728 --> 00:22:10,963
And, unfortunately for you,

550
00:22:10,997 --> 00:22:12,465
I'm no mouse.

551
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:15,902
(Sinnerman laughing)

552
00:22:15,935 --> 00:22:18,004
And, unfortunately for you,

553
00:22:18,037 --> 00:22:21,708
that's a foot
of reinforced steel.

554
00:22:21,741 --> 00:22:23,610
Takes a little extra

555
00:22:23,643 --> 00:22:25,011
to hold the Devil.

556
00:22:25,044 --> 00:22:28,448
Who are you?

557
00:22:28,481 --> 00:22:31,618
How did you return my wings
and steal my face?

558
00:22:31,651 --> 00:22:33,085
Hmm.

559
00:22:33,119 --> 00:22:34,854
You're just chock-full

560
00:22:34,887 --> 00:22:36,022
of questions, aren't you?

561
00:22:36,055 --> 00:22:38,625
Questions I'll answer
in time,

562
00:22:38,658 --> 00:22:40,727
'cause you should have
plenty of that.

563
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:44,531
This place has been abandoned
for at least ten years.

564
00:22:44,564 --> 00:22:47,534
Maybe they'll knock it down
with you still in it.

565
00:22:49,702 --> 00:22:52,472
I tell you what, why don't you
take your sunglasses off, hmm?

566
00:22:52,505 --> 00:22:55,508
Then we can have
a proper conversation.

567
00:22:57,176 --> 00:23:00,813
Want to do your little
desire shtick?

568
00:23:00,847 --> 00:23:03,483
Let me save us both
some time.

569
00:23:03,516 --> 00:23:08,521
I like redheads, strawberries,
and long walks on the beach.

570
00:23:09,756 --> 00:23:12,191
I've got work to do,
now that you're all checked in.

571
00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:14,994
I don't have time
for parlor tricks.

572
00:23:15,027 --> 00:23:17,730
Right.

573
00:23:17,764 --> 00:23:19,832
You hide behind your glasses,

574
00:23:19,866 --> 00:23:22,068
but know this--

575
00:23:22,101 --> 00:23:24,504
when I find out what someone
truly desires,

576
00:23:24,537 --> 00:23:26,806
I find out their
greatest weakness.

577
00:23:26,839 --> 00:23:30,076
And that's not a parlor trick,
Sinnerman.

578
00:23:30,109 --> 00:23:31,511
It's power.

579
00:23:31,544 --> 00:23:32,912
Hmm.

580
00:23:32,945 --> 00:23:34,213
And I promise you

581
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:37,817
I will find out
what you really want,

582
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:40,052
and when I do,

583
00:23:40,086 --> 00:23:42,655
I'm going to use it
to destroy you.

584
00:23:42,689 --> 00:23:45,492
Yeah.

585
00:23:47,093 --> 00:23:49,996
I'm right here, pal.
(chuckles)

586
00:23:50,029 --> 00:23:51,498
What do you got?

587
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:54,601
Too slow.

588
00:23:54,634 --> 00:23:56,536
Why?!

589
00:23:58,237 --> 00:23:59,672
Why are you doing this?

590
00:23:59,706 --> 00:24:02,041
You'll see.

591
00:24:02,074 --> 00:24:03,175
No!

592
00:24:04,844 --> 00:24:06,546
CHLOE: (sighs)
The reason I asked you

593
00:24:06,579 --> 00:24:08,147
to come along is 'cause
you know Frankie.

594
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:09,982
I really need you
to work that connection.

595
00:24:10,016 --> 00:24:11,250
He won't know what hit him.

596
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:14,253
Wait. Can you
stick to the script

597
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:17,023
and say exactly what
I told you to say?

598
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:18,925
Well, of course.
I'm not an idiot.

599
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:20,459
Let's go.

600
00:24:26,599 --> 00:24:28,701
Last time we talked,
you wished there was a way

601
00:24:28,735 --> 00:24:30,136
that you could help
with Joey's death.

602
00:24:30,169 --> 00:24:31,871
Well, there is.

603
00:24:31,904 --> 00:24:33,673
Our prime suspect is

604
00:24:33,706 --> 00:24:36,843
a criminal who calls himself
the Sinnerman.

605
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:42,715
* Yes, there she is

606
00:24:42,749 --> 00:24:43,816
Doesn't ring a bell.

607
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:45,117
CHARLOTTE:
Frankie,

608
00:24:45,151 --> 00:24:47,119
you know that you
and your people

609
00:24:47,153 --> 00:24:48,721
are not under
investigation here.

610
00:24:48,755 --> 00:24:50,189
We just want a way
to find this guy.

611
00:24:50,222 --> 00:24:54,761
The Sinnerman is known
to have entrepreneurial ties.

612
00:24:54,794 --> 00:24:56,529
Did you ever
cross paths with him?

613
00:24:56,563 --> 00:24:59,031
Well, Louie here crosses paths
with the Cinnabon once a week.

614
00:24:59,065 --> 00:25:00,900
Can't get enough of 'em.
Am I right, Louie?

615
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:02,602
(laughs): Yeah.

616
00:25:02,635 --> 00:25:05,972
If you help us out, I promise
it'll be worth your while.

617
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:07,306
Charlotte, we can't do that.
Look,

618
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:10,042
Frankie, come on, handy
for an entrepreneur like you

619
00:25:10,076 --> 00:25:11,611
to have friends
in the DA's office.

620
00:25:12,945 --> 00:25:14,647
* A romance we have...

621
00:25:14,681 --> 00:25:15,548
Sorry, ladies.

622
00:25:15,582 --> 00:25:17,249
Wish I could help.
Cut the crap, Frankie.

623
00:25:17,283 --> 00:25:19,118
Give us something.
Charlotte...

624
00:25:20,219 --> 00:25:22,021
Thank you, Mr. Ferrante,
for your time.

625
00:25:22,054 --> 00:25:23,055
* It remains a mystery

626
00:25:23,089 --> 00:25:24,090
Good evening, gentlemen.

627
00:25:24,123 --> 00:25:25,558
Good night, ladies.

628
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:30,162
* Right there she is...

629
00:25:30,196 --> 00:25:32,131
I'm sorry,
Detective Decker.

630
00:25:32,164 --> 00:25:34,166
I know I went off
script a bit,

631
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,669
but I wanted to get
you what you needed.

632
00:25:36,703 --> 00:25:37,670
And I didn't.

633
00:25:37,704 --> 00:25:38,971
Charlotte,
are you kidding me?

634
00:25:39,005 --> 00:25:40,573
You were perfect.

635
00:25:40,607 --> 00:25:43,142
Frankie had to make sure that
we weren't coming after him,

636
00:25:43,175 --> 00:25:45,344
and coming from you,
he believed it.

637
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:47,680
Mobsters like that--
they don't talk to the cops.

638
00:25:47,714 --> 00:25:49,215
Then what was the point of that?

639
00:25:49,248 --> 00:25:51,818
How does this get us any closer
to the Sinnerman?

640
00:25:51,851 --> 00:25:53,152
Frankie obviously
cares about Joey.

641
00:25:53,185 --> 00:25:54,687
He's gonna want to get revenge.

642
00:25:54,721 --> 00:25:56,956
I think he's gonna find
the Sinnerman on his own.

643
00:25:56,989 --> 00:25:58,991
And when he does...

644
00:25:59,025 --> 00:26:00,593
you'll be waiting.

645
00:26:01,861 --> 00:26:04,931
You expected me
to fail, didn't you?

646
00:26:04,964 --> 00:26:07,867
Why didn't you just
trust me with the truth?

647
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:09,301
Charlotte, you know
the things you've done.

648
00:26:09,335 --> 00:26:11,971
You know the reasons
I can't trust you.

649
00:26:12,004 --> 00:26:15,675
Huh. I suppose... I do.

650
00:26:15,708 --> 00:26:16,909
And, look, I want to believe

651
00:26:16,943 --> 00:26:18,678
that this change of heart
is for real,

652
00:26:18,711 --> 00:26:22,114
but you're gonna have to
earn that trust back, okay?

653
00:26:22,148 --> 00:26:23,816
This is a good start, though.

654
00:26:25,985 --> 00:26:28,621
I got to stay here
and watch Frankie,

655
00:26:28,655 --> 00:26:31,958
but let me call you a car,
get you a ride home.

656
00:26:31,991 --> 00:26:33,726
I'll find my own way home.

657
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:34,994
Good night.

658
00:26:35,027 --> 00:26:37,596
Oh. Night.

659
00:26:38,898 --> 00:26:42,234
(phone vibrates)

660
00:26:42,268 --> 00:26:43,836
(scoffs)

661
00:26:43,870 --> 00:26:44,871
Hey, Pierce.

662
00:26:44,904 --> 00:26:47,006
PIERCE: You still working
that Ferrante angle?

663
00:26:47,039 --> 00:26:48,641
Uh, yeah, I am.

664
00:26:48,675 --> 00:26:50,376
It's turned into a stakeout.
But why?

665
00:26:50,409 --> 00:26:52,879
'Cause I brought food.

666
00:26:54,947 --> 00:26:56,916
Mind if I join you?

667
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:03,823
Come on.

668
00:27:03,856 --> 00:27:05,658
Oh...

669
00:27:05,692 --> 00:27:07,359
So this is
your diabolical plan?

670
00:27:07,393 --> 00:27:09,195
Is it? Hmm?

671
00:27:09,228 --> 00:27:11,197
To bore me to death?!

672
00:27:11,230 --> 00:27:13,032
(sighs)

673
00:27:13,065 --> 00:27:15,401
WOMAN:
Lucifer?

674
00:27:15,434 --> 00:27:18,270
Lucifer, I know
you're in here.

675
00:27:18,304 --> 00:27:19,972
In here!

676
00:27:22,341 --> 00:27:24,310
(door creaks)

677
00:27:24,343 --> 00:27:25,444
Maze!

678
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:28,380
Oh, you're a sight
for sore eyes.

679
00:27:28,414 --> 00:27:30,116
I didn't realize
you still kept tabs on me.

680
00:27:30,149 --> 00:27:31,784
What are you
talking about?

681
00:27:31,818 --> 00:27:34,286
I tracked you down because I
have a bone to pick with you.

682
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,789
What?
I asked you to talk.

683
00:27:36,823 --> 00:27:40,226
And you blow me off
and hide in a freezer?

684
00:27:40,259 --> 00:27:42,328
I thought we were
past all of this.

685
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:44,797
Oh, sure, yeah, thought
I'd just hang around in here

686
00:27:44,831 --> 00:27:47,399
like a frozen side of beef
just to avoid you. (laughs)

687
00:27:47,433 --> 00:27:50,269
Hello! I was a prisoner!

688
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:52,204
The Sinnerman had me
trapped here.

689
00:27:52,238 --> 00:27:53,439
Uh...

690
00:27:53,472 --> 00:27:55,207
Now would you please
just stand aside?

691
00:27:55,241 --> 00:27:56,943
I need to figure out
what he's up to,

692
00:27:56,976 --> 00:27:59,011
and I've already lost
enough time as it is.

693
00:27:59,045 --> 00:28:00,279
Hang on. You were trapped?

694
00:28:00,312 --> 00:28:02,882
Well, obviously!

695
00:28:07,119 --> 00:28:07,987
Maze!

696
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:10,322
(banging on door)

697
00:28:10,356 --> 00:28:12,091
Oh, for...

698
00:28:15,995 --> 00:28:18,865
LUCIFER: Maze! Come on, open up!
(banging on door)

699
00:28:18,898 --> 00:28:21,233
I've got places to go,
people to hurt!

700
00:28:21,267 --> 00:28:24,837
Just think of someone else's
needs for a change!

701
00:28:24,871 --> 00:28:26,505
Can you hear?

702
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:29,075
You're going nowhere, Lucifer.

703
00:28:29,108 --> 00:28:33,379
You don't get out until you
listen to what I have to say,

704
00:28:33,412 --> 00:28:36,115
and act like you care.

705
00:28:36,148 --> 00:28:37,817
(laughs)

706
00:28:37,850 --> 00:28:40,252
(quietly):
Can't believe this.

707
00:28:40,286 --> 00:28:42,221
(sighs)

708
00:28:44,456 --> 00:28:46,125
What's on your mind, Maze?

709
00:28:46,158 --> 00:28:50,229
Did you know that Linda
and Amenadiel are a thing?

710
00:28:51,397 --> 00:28:53,232
Linda and Amenadiel
are doing what now?

711
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:55,367
How'd you know?
What makes you say that?

712
00:28:55,401 --> 00:28:56,468
Well, I saw them

713
00:28:56,502 --> 00:28:58,170
in her office.

714
00:28:58,204 --> 00:29:00,539
"Talking."

715
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,408
They were clearly about to bone.

716
00:29:02,441 --> 00:29:04,376
Right, you do realize

717
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:07,847
that talking in her office
is literally Linda's job?

718
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:13,319
Interesting point.

719
00:29:13,352 --> 00:29:14,921
Hmm, isn't it?

720
00:29:14,954 --> 00:29:16,288
And, you know, so what

721
00:29:16,322 --> 00:29:18,958
if Amenadiel is playing doctor
with the doctor?

722
00:29:18,991 --> 00:29:20,559
So our old flames
are having a fling.

723
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:22,194
I don't care.
Why should you?

724
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:26,332
Unless...

725
00:29:26,365 --> 00:29:27,834
(laughs)

726
00:29:27,867 --> 00:29:30,236
Unless you're still hot
for angel?

727
00:29:30,269 --> 00:29:31,437
No!
No?

728
00:29:31,470 --> 00:29:32,939
No!
Ah.

729
00:29:32,972 --> 00:29:34,941
Well, I...
I mean, she's just...

730
00:29:34,974 --> 00:29:37,810
my best friend, and he's my ex.

731
00:29:37,844 --> 00:29:39,211
I don't like it.

732
00:29:39,245 --> 00:29:41,981
So, you don't want him,
but nobody else can have him.

733
00:29:42,014 --> 00:29:43,315
That's awfully greedy
of you, Maze.

734
00:29:43,349 --> 00:29:45,351
I've been gone
for too long, okay?

735
00:29:45,384 --> 00:29:48,554
I just need to know
what the hell is going on.

736
00:29:48,587 --> 00:29:51,357
And what would you do
if you knew?

737
00:29:51,390 --> 00:29:53,926
Hmm?

738
00:29:56,395 --> 00:30:00,132
Look, you really want
my advice, Mazikeen?

739
00:30:00,166 --> 00:30:03,970
Ask yourself
what you truly desire.

740
00:30:04,003 --> 00:30:05,938
And be honest.
Otherwise, there's no point.

741
00:30:09,241 --> 00:30:11,210
Maze?

742
00:30:11,243 --> 00:30:13,245
Mazikeen?

743
00:30:13,279 --> 00:30:15,247
You still there?

744
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:18,150
(door unlocks)

745
00:30:22,955 --> 00:30:24,123
Thanks, Lucifer.

746
00:30:24,156 --> 00:30:26,458
Great talk.
Glad I could help. Got to go.

747
00:30:29,061 --> 00:30:30,997
PIERCE:
I wonder when Frankie's

748
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:32,865
gonna make his move.

749
00:30:32,899 --> 00:30:35,401
Soon. Bet they're reaching
out to their sources,

750
00:30:35,434 --> 00:30:37,436
probably calling the
Sinnerman right now.

751
00:30:37,469 --> 00:30:39,371
(indistinct radio chatter)

752
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:43,943
All right.

753
00:30:43,976 --> 00:30:45,611
Out with it, Decker.

754
00:30:45,644 --> 00:30:47,346
I either have food
in my teeth,

755
00:30:47,379 --> 00:30:49,481
or you have something
you want to say to me.

756
00:30:51,050 --> 00:30:53,552
Why is this case
so important to you?

757
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:55,421
It's not.

758
00:30:55,454 --> 00:30:57,223
It's a high-priority case,
and...

759
00:30:59,125 --> 00:31:00,326
I need to display leadership

760
00:31:00,359 --> 00:31:02,394
to the suits downtown.
That's all.

761
00:31:02,428 --> 00:31:05,631
Really? Showing up out of
nowhere while I'm on a stakeout?

762
00:31:05,664 --> 00:31:07,199
You said it yourself.

763
00:31:07,233 --> 00:31:10,069
You and the Sinnerman
crossed paths in Chicago.

764
00:31:10,102 --> 00:31:11,203
This is personal,
isn't it?

765
00:31:11,237 --> 00:31:14,173
(indistinct radio chatter)

766
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:16,308
It is.

767
00:31:17,209 --> 00:31:19,578
The Sinnerman killed my brother.

768
00:31:22,381 --> 00:31:24,350
I'm sorry.

769
00:31:26,352 --> 00:31:29,488
I thought I could run away
from the pain of it.

770
00:31:29,521 --> 00:31:31,557
From him.

771
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:34,326
Now I know that I can't anymore,

772
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:38,497
so I need to find him and
make him pay for what he did.

773
00:31:40,166 --> 00:31:43,602
Do you know why
I asked for that personal day?

774
00:31:43,635 --> 00:31:45,604
The anniversary of

775
00:31:45,637 --> 00:31:47,606
my father's death is coming up.

776
00:31:49,075 --> 00:31:51,277
And, uh, he was killed on duty.

777
00:31:53,045 --> 00:31:55,147
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

778
00:31:55,181 --> 00:31:56,615
It was a long time ago.

779
00:31:56,648 --> 00:31:58,951
But just a few months ago,

780
00:31:58,985 --> 00:32:01,087
we finally found
the guy who did it.

781
00:32:02,288 --> 00:32:05,124
And I had dreamed of
that moment for so long.

782
00:32:05,157 --> 00:32:06,993
Also kind of dreaded it.

783
00:32:07,026 --> 00:32:10,129
I mean, he caused my
family so much pain.

784
00:32:10,162 --> 00:32:13,165
When I finally
found him, I...

785
00:32:13,199 --> 00:32:15,267
I didn't know
what I'd do.

786
00:32:15,301 --> 00:32:17,136
What did you do?

787
00:32:17,169 --> 00:32:20,172
I did the right thing.

788
00:32:20,206 --> 00:32:22,174
I arrested him.

789
00:32:22,208 --> 00:32:24,110
But it wasn't easy.

790
00:32:25,577 --> 00:32:27,346
I get it.

791
00:32:27,379 --> 00:32:31,183
I know why you don't talk
about this stuff.

792
00:32:31,217 --> 00:32:34,686
(exhales) I don't, either,
not even to Lucifer.

793
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:37,489
It's just too painful.

794
00:32:40,426 --> 00:32:42,428
Think about what
you really want.

795
00:32:44,530 --> 00:32:47,433
Don't do anything
you're gonna regret.

796
00:32:47,466 --> 00:32:49,568
(sighs)

797
00:32:49,601 --> 00:32:52,304
I guess I have
to give you

798
00:32:52,338 --> 00:32:53,672
that personal day now.

799
00:32:53,705 --> 00:32:55,341
(chuckles lightly)

800
00:32:56,308 --> 00:32:58,310
Heads up, we got someone.

801
00:32:58,344 --> 00:33:00,412
He doesn't look
like a mobster.

802
00:33:00,446 --> 00:33:02,714
Maybe one of their sources.
Let's hang tight.

803
00:33:02,748 --> 00:33:04,116
Copy that.
(phone vibrates)

804
00:33:04,150 --> 00:33:05,484
Lucifer.

805
00:33:05,517 --> 00:33:06,518
Detective.

806
00:33:06,552 --> 00:33:08,554
Finally. Look,
I'm on a stakeout.

807
00:33:08,587 --> 00:33:10,122
You were right.

808
00:33:10,156 --> 00:33:11,257
The Sinnerman
is behind this.

809
00:33:11,290 --> 00:33:12,424
You don't say.

810
00:33:12,458 --> 00:33:14,160
I've just gotten
out of cold storage

811
00:33:14,193 --> 00:33:15,327
after being grabbed
by him again.

812
00:33:15,361 --> 00:33:17,429
What? Are you okay?
LUCIFER: I'm fine.

813
00:33:17,463 --> 00:33:20,432
Just dying to crush that
pathetic excuse for a man.

814
00:33:20,466 --> 00:33:22,601
You saw him? What
does he look like?

815
00:33:22,634 --> 00:33:24,336
Black fellow, early 40s,

816
00:33:24,370 --> 00:33:25,704
though he dresses
like an old man.

817
00:33:25,737 --> 00:33:27,606
Would you believe
he wore a sweater vest?

818
00:33:27,639 --> 00:33:29,141
His greatest crime yet.

819
00:33:29,175 --> 00:33:31,177
CHLOE: That's not a source;
that's him.

820
00:33:31,743 --> 00:33:33,479
Let's go.

821
00:33:33,512 --> 00:33:35,247
Wait, Detective.

822
00:33:35,281 --> 00:33:37,083
Detective?
(gunshots)

823
00:33:37,116 --> 00:33:39,051
(gunshots)

824
00:33:39,085 --> 00:33:41,187
Bloody hell.

825
00:33:47,493 --> 00:33:50,296
(Frankie groaning)

826
00:33:54,233 --> 00:33:56,535
Drop the weapon.
(gunshots)

827
00:33:59,105 --> 00:34:00,172
I'm on him! Cut him off!

828
00:34:00,206 --> 00:34:01,673
Chloe, wait!

829
00:34:07,179 --> 00:34:08,380
(gunshot)

830
00:34:11,817 --> 00:34:13,785
(gunshot)

831
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:17,489
(gunshot)

832
00:34:17,523 --> 00:34:20,426
We've got units outside!

833
00:34:20,459 --> 00:34:23,095
If you give up now,
we can take you in safely.

834
00:34:23,129 --> 00:34:24,696
But this is so much fun.

835
00:34:24,730 --> 00:34:26,432
(gunshots)

836
00:34:26,465 --> 00:34:29,635
(whispering):
Oh. Where are you?

837
00:34:29,668 --> 00:34:32,304
Where are you?

838
00:34:36,742 --> 00:34:37,676
(gunshot)

839
00:34:43,282 --> 00:34:45,384
(gunshot)

840
00:34:55,427 --> 00:34:57,563
(panting)

841
00:35:00,366 --> 00:35:02,801
Do what you got to do.

842
00:35:03,869 --> 00:35:05,404
Pierce, wait.

843
00:35:09,708 --> 00:35:12,144
Hey.

844
00:35:12,178 --> 00:35:13,812
Let me help you.

845
00:35:18,184 --> 00:35:19,451
(groans)

846
00:35:20,919 --> 00:35:23,189
You already did.

847
00:35:23,222 --> 00:35:25,191
(grunts)

848
00:35:26,358 --> 00:35:28,394
You're under arrest.

849
00:35:28,427 --> 00:35:30,462
Let's go.
(handcuffs tighten)

850
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:36,568
(indistinct police radio
chatter)

851
00:35:43,342 --> 00:35:45,777
(tires squeal, engine turns off)

852
00:35:47,979 --> 00:35:49,381
Detective.

853
00:35:49,415 --> 00:35:52,351
You're okay. What happened?

854
00:35:52,384 --> 00:35:53,519
We got him.
What?

855
00:35:53,552 --> 00:35:55,554
You did it.
You got the Sinnerman.

856
00:35:55,587 --> 00:35:58,657
Actually, Pierce did.

857
00:35:59,925 --> 00:36:01,660
Right.

858
00:36:01,693 --> 00:36:03,662
Right. Well,
where-where is he?

859
00:36:04,796 --> 00:36:06,465
He's, um...

860
00:36:06,498 --> 00:36:07,799
(exhales)

861
00:36:09,701 --> 00:36:11,403
I want to talk to him.

862
00:36:13,239 --> 00:36:14,840
Lucifer.

863
00:36:14,873 --> 00:36:16,475
Don't worry.

864
00:36:16,508 --> 00:36:18,244
You'll get your chance.

865
00:36:18,277 --> 00:36:19,811
Officer, he's ready.

866
00:36:39,431 --> 00:36:41,633
Linda, you there?

867
00:36:45,337 --> 00:36:46,572
What's up?

868
00:36:46,605 --> 00:36:48,707
Are you alone?

869
00:36:49,608 --> 00:36:51,377
Yeah. Why?

870
00:36:51,410 --> 00:36:55,247
'Cause you're acting
kind of strange.

871
00:36:55,281 --> 00:36:56,715
What's going on?

872
00:36:58,817 --> 00:36:59,918
Uh...

873
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,722
I should have told
you this earlier,

874
00:37:03,755 --> 00:37:07,559
but it was... weird

875
00:37:07,593 --> 00:37:11,430
seeing you and Amenadiel so...
chummy.

876
00:37:11,463 --> 00:37:13,899
Oh. Were we?

877
00:37:13,932 --> 00:37:15,901
Yeah, you were.

878
00:37:15,934 --> 00:37:18,404
Made me feel like beating
the crap out of him.

879
00:37:18,437 --> 00:37:21,273
Or at least
throwing rocks at cars.

880
00:37:21,307 --> 00:37:22,508
But, no, I didn't.

881
00:37:23,509 --> 00:37:25,411
I came to tell you how I feel.

882
00:37:25,444 --> 00:37:26,612
Yes.

883
00:37:26,645 --> 00:37:28,980
Please. Tell me.

884
00:37:30,516 --> 00:37:32,851
Okay. Um...

885
00:37:32,884 --> 00:37:36,755
I've been thinking
about it all day.

886
00:37:36,788 --> 00:37:39,391
You're my best friend, you know?

887
00:37:39,425 --> 00:37:41,427
And he's my ex.
(chuckles)

888
00:37:41,460 --> 00:37:43,462
And by-by "ex," I mean, like,

889
00:37:43,495 --> 00:37:46,298
one of a million
ex-sexual partners

890
00:37:46,332 --> 00:37:49,735
and not anything special.

891
00:37:49,768 --> 00:37:53,839
Any-Anyway, um...

892
00:37:53,872 --> 00:37:57,876
it makes me feel left out.

893
00:37:57,909 --> 00:38:01,079
So I don't want you two
getting together

894
00:38:01,112 --> 00:38:03,048
if that's possible.

895
00:38:05,083 --> 00:38:06,051
I understand.

896
00:38:07,886 --> 00:38:09,988
You have nothing to worry about.

897
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:12,958
Thank you.

898
00:38:12,991 --> 00:38:16,795
(sighs) I figured you wouldn't
want my sloppy seconds, anyway.

899
00:38:16,828 --> 00:38:20,632
And you know me,
I was all over that angel.

900
00:38:20,666 --> 00:38:21,933
I went in deep.

901
00:38:21,967 --> 00:38:24,370
Used every tool

902
00:38:24,403 --> 00:38:26,037
in that Swiss Army knife.

903
00:38:26,071 --> 00:38:27,739
Know what I mean?

904
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:32,444
I touched nerves that he never
knew he had.

905
00:38:32,478 --> 00:38:34,613
I can only imagine.

906
00:38:34,646 --> 00:38:36,382
(laughing):
Yeah.

907
00:38:36,415 --> 00:38:37,683
Anyway...

908
00:38:40,519 --> 00:38:41,953
You're the best, Linda.

909
00:38:47,393 --> 00:38:49,528
(crying)

910
00:38:49,561 --> 00:38:52,398
(door opens and closes)

911
00:38:52,431 --> 00:38:54,332
DAN:
You okay in there?

912
00:38:55,767 --> 00:38:57,969
Um... (sniffles)

913
00:38:58,003 --> 00:38:59,838
I'm-I'm fine.

914
00:38:59,871 --> 00:39:03,575
Thank you, Detective Espinoza.

915
00:39:03,609 --> 00:39:04,843
Charlotte?

916
00:39:04,876 --> 00:39:06,745
CHARLOTTE: I just needed
a moment. (sniffles)

917
00:39:06,778 --> 00:39:09,080
And I thought that this was...

918
00:39:09,114 --> 00:39:12,551
the one place that
I wouldn't be disturbed.

919
00:39:12,584 --> 00:39:15,421
DAN:
I don't want to pry, but, uh,

920
00:39:15,454 --> 00:39:18,023
you don't seem fine.

921
00:39:18,056 --> 00:39:19,558
(sniffling)

922
00:39:19,591 --> 00:39:22,661
(sighing):
I'm not.

923
00:39:22,694 --> 00:39:24,830
I switched to prosecution

924
00:39:24,863 --> 00:39:26,898
to try and be
a better person...

925
00:39:26,932 --> 00:39:28,967
but I'm not
helping anyone.

926
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:32,871
I just keep screwing
things up. (sniffles)

927
00:39:32,904 --> 00:39:37,108
I was really good
at being the old me.

928
00:39:37,142 --> 00:39:39,978
The best.

929
00:39:40,011 --> 00:39:44,550
But I know I need
to make a change.

930
00:39:44,583 --> 00:39:47,853
And I suck at it.

931
00:39:49,855 --> 00:39:53,024
No one expects you
to change overnight.

932
00:39:54,826 --> 00:39:58,464
It's hard to be one
of the good guys.

933
00:39:58,497 --> 00:40:00,466
Look, I screw up, too.

934
00:40:00,499 --> 00:40:03,869
I've made plenty of mistakes,
believe me.

935
00:40:03,902 --> 00:40:07,172
But I don't quit...

936
00:40:07,205 --> 00:40:09,808
and I know that
counts for something.

937
00:40:11,910 --> 00:40:13,779
At least you're trying, right?

938
00:40:20,852 --> 00:40:22,120
(chuckles lightly)

939
00:40:26,191 --> 00:40:27,526
Thank you, Dan.

940
00:40:27,559 --> 00:40:29,695
Don't mention it.

941
00:40:29,728 --> 00:40:31,830
(door opens)

942
00:40:33,532 --> 00:40:35,501
Oh, hey, Hernandez.

943
00:40:38,637 --> 00:40:40,606
I'm in the men's room,
aren't I?

944
00:40:40,639 --> 00:40:41,773
Oh, yeah.

945
00:40:41,807 --> 00:40:44,009
(laughs)

946
00:40:47,713 --> 00:40:49,815
*

947
00:40:57,956 --> 00:41:01,793
* What happens in the shadows

948
00:41:01,827 --> 00:41:04,830
* No one has to know

949
00:41:04,863 --> 00:41:06,998
* The truth is in the gallows

950
00:41:09,535 --> 00:41:12,804
* It'll burn
but it won't let go *

951
00:41:12,838 --> 00:41:15,741
* A whisper in the darkness

952
00:41:15,774 --> 00:41:18,710
* In the quiet it'll grow

953
00:41:18,744 --> 00:41:19,911
* You try to hide it

954
00:41:19,945 --> 00:41:22,914
* In the farthest place

955
00:41:22,948 --> 00:41:27,485
* But everybody knows

956
00:41:29,087 --> 00:41:33,559
* There's something
in the shadows *

957
00:41:33,592 --> 00:41:36,928
* Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh

958
00:41:36,962 --> 00:41:40,866
* Cuts you like an arrow

959
00:41:40,899 --> 00:41:43,935
* Shifting through the dark

960
00:41:43,969 --> 00:41:48,707
* Your strength is in
your weakness *

961
00:41:48,740 --> 00:41:52,043
* This fire in your blood

962
00:41:52,077 --> 00:41:55,313
* Hanging from that hope

963
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:58,016
* But everybody knows

964
00:41:58,049 --> 00:42:00,185
* There's something
in the shadows *

965
00:42:02,153 --> 00:42:03,822
My, my...

966
00:42:03,855 --> 00:42:06,625
how the tables have turned.

967
00:42:06,658 --> 00:42:10,829
I don't know if you remember,
but I made you a promise:

968
00:42:10,862 --> 00:42:13,098
to look into your eyes
and find out

969
00:42:13,131 --> 00:42:16,334
what the great Sinnerman
desires...

970
00:42:16,367 --> 00:42:18,069
and then take it from him.

971
00:42:19,638 --> 00:42:21,607
* There's something
in the shadows *

972
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:24,275
I'm a man of my word,
so let's get to it, shall we?

973
00:42:25,944 --> 00:42:28,079
Look at me.

974
00:42:30,281 --> 00:42:32,884
Look into my eyes!

975
00:42:32,918 --> 00:42:36,822
* There's something
in the shadows *

976
00:42:36,855 --> 00:42:39,991
* Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh

977
00:42:40,025 --> 00:42:42,928
* Cuts you like an arrow

978
00:42:45,897 --> 00:42:47,899
* Shifting through the dark

979
00:42:47,933 --> 00:42:50,669
Now...

980
00:42:50,702 --> 00:42:53,605
you'll never know what I want.

981
00:42:53,639 --> 00:42:55,106
But...

982
00:42:55,140 --> 00:42:57,275
* Hanging from that hope

983
00:42:57,308 --> 00:42:59,177
Call Chloe!

984
00:42:59,210 --> 00:43:00,345
Chloe!

985
00:43:00,378 --> 00:43:01,346
Tell Chloe!

986
00:43:01,379 --> 00:43:04,349
Somebody get a
medic in here!

987
00:43:04,382 --> 00:43:06,251
(laughs)

